com.leantegra.wibeat.sdk

Class VenueManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.leantegra.wibeat.sdk.VenueManager

  • public class VenueManager
extends Object
    Allows to get and synchronize a Venue setup from CVO portal with current SDK credentials.

    Note: Venue setup will be cached in device.
    If you change the SDK credentials, please call the clear() method.
    Since:
    1.4.0

    • Method Detail

      • runSynchronization

        public boolean runSynchronization()
        Run a Venue synchronization with CVO portal.
        When the Venue setup update the VENUE_UPDATED_ACTION broadcast will be sent.
        When the WiBeat setup update the WI_BEATS_UPDATED_ACTION broadcast will be sent.
        Returns:
        true if a synchronization started successfully, false if it already run.

      • getVenue

        public Venue getVenue()
        Returns a Venue setup for current SDK credentials.
        Returns:
        the Venue object or null if Venue setup not synchronized. Call the runSynchronization() method to load Venue setup.

      • getWiBeatList

        public List<WiBeat> getWiBeatList()
        Returns a WiBeat setup for current SDK credentials.
        Returns:
        the WiBeat list or null if WiBeat setup is empty or not synchronized. Call the runSynchronization() method to load all Venue setup.

      • clear

        public void clear()
        Clear the Venue setup cache. Call the runSynchronization() method to load new Venue setup.
